article_metadata.description: Millions of people could qualify for federal subsidies that will pay the entire monthly cost of some health-care plans being offered in the online marketplaces set up under President Barack Obama’s health-care law, a surprising figure that has not gotten much attention, in part because the zero-premium plans come with serious trade-offs.
